OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F396A1776600665
OL,3,CUK Govt 'unable to recommend' Isle of
OL,4,CMan's assisted dying bill
OL,6,FChanges could be made to the Isle of
OL,7,FMan's assisted dying law after the UK
OL,8,FGovernment said it would not be
OL,9,Frecommended for Royal Assent 'at this
OL,10,Ftime'.
OL,12,FThe Manx Government said its received
OL,13,Fcorrespondence from the UK Deputy
OL,14,FPrime Minister in his capacity as Lord
OL,15,FChancellor and Privy Council's adviser
OL,16,Fto The King on matters relating to the
OL,17,FCrown Dependencies.
OL,19,FThe letter confirms that the Ministry
OL,20,Fof Justice is unable to recommend the
OL,21,FBill for Royal Assent.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/6
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,397,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F396A1776600665
OL,3,CUK Govt 'unable to recommend' Isle of
OL,4,CMan's assisted dying bill
OL,6,FJustice Secretary David Lammy said
OL,7,Fthere may not be enough protections to
OL,8,Fcomply with the European Convention on
OL,9,FHuman Rights.
OL,11,FThe Island's government said the
OL,12,Fletter is "in line with the UK's long-
OL,13,Fstanding responsibilities towards the
OL,14,FCrown Dependencies."
OL,16,FThe last time Royal Assent was
OL,17,Fwithheld was in 1972.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/6
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
