FL,397,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F396A1776600665
OL,3,CUK Govt 'unable to recommend' Isle of
OL,4,CMan's assisted dying bill
OL,6,FA statement from the Isle of Man
OL,7,FGovernment on Friday said: "The
OL,8,FMinistry of Justice duly consulted
OL,9,Fwith the Isle of Man Government,
OL,10,Fseeking clarity on the proposed
OL,11,Farrangements for: the independent
OL,12,Fmonitoring of assisted deaths;
OL,13,Fsafeguards against coercion; and
OL,14,Fensuring that individuals have the
OL,15,Fcapacity to make informed decisions
OL,16,Fregarding assisted dying.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/6
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,397,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F396A1776600665
OL,3,CUK Govt 'unable to recommend' Isle of
OL,4,CMan's assisted dying bill
OL,6,F"The consultation culminated in the
OL,7,FIsle of Man Government providing
OL,8,Fcomprehensive assurances outlining a
OL,9,Fnumber of commitments intended to
OL,10,Faddress the issues raised.
OL,12,F"While these commitments would, if
OL,13,Ffully implemented, mitigate the legal
OL,14,Frisk significantly, they do not form
OL,15,Fpart of the Bill.
OL,17,F"It is therefore the UK Government's
OL,18,Fview that these matters must be
OL,19,Faddressed directly on the face of the
OL,20,FBill to comply with the European
OL,21,FConvention on Human Rights.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/6
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,397,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F396A1776600665
OL,3,CUK Govt 'unable to recommend' Isle of
OL,4,CMan's assisted dying bill
OL,6,F"It is on this basis that the Ministry
OL,7,Fof Justice is unable to recommend the
OL,8,FBill for Royal Assent at this time."
OL,10,FThe statement went on to say the
OL,11,Fdecision "should not be interpreted as
OL,12,Fdisallowing Royal Assent" and it's not
OL,13,Fa reflection on the merits of assisted
OL,14,Fdying.
OL,16,FThe government went on: It reflects
OL,17,Fsolely the need to ensure that the
OL,18,Flegislation, once enacted, contains
OL,19,Fthe necessary protections required
OL,20,Funder the European Convention on Human
OL,21,FRights."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/6
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
